description: Grounding, answers. Synth tones at beginning lead into textured spacious atmosphere.
Searching, seeking feel. Rising digital arp turns into a wash of notes.
Clarity followed by curious feel. Arp begins then transitions into wash of many layers of delayed notes.
Subconscious, subdued feel. Gentle notes begin then dusty granular shifting drone.
Questioning, wondering feel. Arp begins then transitions into long droning notes.
Mellow but inquisitive feel. Long dusty crushed chord flourishes.
Disjointed yet calm feel. Minimal synth tones with lots of space between.
Darker yet relaxed feel. Lo Fi Music box kind of feel with bell like tones.
Reaching unstable feel. Strong monophonic synth melody with lots of delay and texture beneath.
Upbeat energetic feel. Minimal synth art bounce along gently.
Dreamy yet energetic. Minimal synth arp with delay chugs along.
Ungrounded yet beautiful. Synth notes unsteadily granulate.
Expansive and digital. Notes pluck with massive reverb, like a giant digital cavern.
Stuck in a swarm. A droning granular note with some digital filtration.
Random glitchiness. Staticy bits and clicks and synth notes jump around.
Holding pattern.  Digital grains stick on same note.
Breaking down but holding on. Lofi synth notes click in and out of noisey texture.
Syncopated pulsing. Hi and low notes dance along to a repetitive pulse.
Muted bell orchestra. Synths knockout muted marimbas and metallophones.
Lonely and ponderous. Single sparse noise synth notes unfold.
Sweet and small. Music box like notes plink along with nostalgia.
Liquid and floating. Synth notes play lightly like flying fairies.
Tiny insectoid. High frequency synth notes with random resonant filtrations.
Rapid yet stuck. Arp notes underneath a single repeating dirty synth note.
Thinking alone with sudden flashes of ideas. Minimal synth arp with occasional bursts of spaciousness.
Time passing alone. A single synth arpeggios on alternating chords.
A dark little synth wonders alone. An arp keeps trying to restart itself but falls apart.
Insistent and determined. Fast paced arp synth.
Confused but okay with it. Long delay cycle of a mix of icy and warm synth tones.
Feeling like a tiny electric angel. Plucked harp with strange reversed echoing notes.
Feeling agitated. Quick little arp pounding at a tiny synth at a fast pulse.
Sitting in kalidoscope of a bamboo garden. Plinking wooden synthy tones with long washy echo.
Dreamy synthy bell like tones gently explore.
Wild and uncharted. Noisey sweeps and unfettered notes slowly shift.
Malfunctioning and erratic but still cheery. Lofi noisey synth tones start and stop almost to a rhythm.
Wandering through a dark labyrinth. Muted stabby artp starts and stops over a quiet melodic synth.
Gentle but strange. Notes click and throb beneath a noisy wash.
Tiny electric train moves through a giant tunnel.  Spacicious echo-y and noisy synths chug along.
Bamboo synths plink away insistently jumping back and forth to different times and places.
Feeling activated but okay about it all. Muted synth arp pulses with a messy rhythm.
Nostalgic strange cheer. Synths and a glockenspiel pulse through wavering tape noise
Break of day. Single piano gently repeats with occasional piano chord flourishes on top.
Anticipation of what's to come. Synth Notes with side chain gate pulses along
Breaking and unstable. Notes shift up and down and get noisey and bloopy with confusion.
Feeling stuck. Noisey loop of lofi broken synths.
Feels hopeful yet nowhere. Noisey loop of some plucking strings and synths.
Suspended in the strange and wondrous. Tiny piano loops, little snips of sped up voices, washy noise.
Open up to the Epic. Droning chiming choir abstracts outwards.
Tiny noisey countryside. Chirping, strumming and sped up plucks and clicks.
Morse code music. Typing out some random clicky pitches.
Feeling a bit blurry and overwhelmed. Barely recognizable piano granulations.
Feeling energized and a bit wild. Strange pulsing piano notes and echoed scrapings.
Expansive and chirpy. Reveberant synths and hi frequency chirps washout.
